RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eli gibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DELTA LADY was sent to share the lead from outside, moved clear when asked upper stretch then continued to open up under mild urging. MINI DRESS prominent from inside, angled out some on the bend, swung out five wide for the drive, rallied the final furlong and got up for second. WITCHING crowded at the break, raced in contention from outside, lost considerable ground fanning widest entering the lane, gradually drifted out upper stretch, held a straight path the last eighth and closed well to finish on even terms with MINI DRESS. ABBMAR vied for the lead between rivals on the backstretch, did not keep up into the turn, took the rail, took over second from just off the inside upper stretch then slowly wore down in the waning yards. SENORITA AURORA moved to the inside early on, waited for room along the rail on the bend, continued to wait for a clear path from inside in the lane then altered outside ABBMAR inside the sixteenth marker. HALLIE'S RAINBOW displayed early speed off the rail but inside rivals then weakened between rivals for the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Hallie's Rainbow
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path speed, weakened between foes stretch

ENTRY.NAME: dh-Mini Dress
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide turn, angled 5 wide into stretch, late run

ENTRY.NAME: dh-Witching
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide turn,swung 6 wide into lane,drifted out some upper stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Abbmar
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed between, inside turn, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Delta Lady
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 3-4 path turn, drew off stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Senorita Aurora
ENTRY.COMMENT: waited inside, altered out inside 1/16

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 50. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LITTLE ACCOUNT stumbled as she broke on top, stalked the early speed from outside, commenced her bid two wide on the bend, floated out some entering the lane, drifted out gradually as she moved ahead upper stretch, held a straight path the last eighth and maintained control. ENVEY N ICE rated from outside, picked up her pace three wide on the bend, swung outside LITTLE ACCOUNT for the stretch run, angled out some as the latter came out, battled for second the final sixteenth and edged ahead for the place in time. JEMEZ FALLS forwardly placed between horses, was two wide taking the turn, rallied belatedly the final furlong, fought for second inside the last sixteenth, was narrowly outfinished but caught ROARINGLIKETHUNDER for third. ROARINGLIKETHUNDER emerged with the early lead from between rivals, saved ground through the bend then gradually wore down for the drive. HUQOOQ chased from inside, angled out with two furlongs to go, came widest into the lane and had no late bid. DART ATTACK was well placed early from inside, did not keep up on the bend, floated out some for the stretch run and continued to fade.

ENTRY.NAME: Dart Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside 1/4, 3-path into stretch, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Huqooq
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, angled out 1/4, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Roaringlikethunder
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, inside turn, weakened stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Jemez Falls
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly between, 2 wide turn, dueled for 2nd late

ENTRY.NAME: Little Account
ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled start, 2-3 path turn, drifted out some upper stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Envey N Ice
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4 path turn, all out outside, closed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 24500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLOEY ATTACK broke on top, quickly moved away from the rest, was asked leaving the bend then maintained full control while kept to urging in the lane. BEST MAN SPEECH was bumped and forced into OSCAR NOMINEE at the break, raced in the second flight from inside, angled outside CLOEY ATTACK upper stretch, could not close the gap on that one but proved easily second best. WILDISH broke outward, starting a chain reaction of bumping, chased CLOEY ATTACK from off the rail, did not keep up two wide on the bend, fanned out further for the drive, began to wear down the last eighth but lasted for the show. IT'S ON lugged in some at the start, chased from midpack, came four wide into the lane and had no late bid. TIGGER ATTACK lost ground widest through the turn then showed belated interest the final furlong. PETE'S LEGACY was void of speed, though hustled along, saved ground taking the turn and failed to have a significant stretch response. DRINKING TOUR crowded at the break, chased from outside and showed little. OSCAR NOMINEE was bumped then steadied back from crowding and never a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Wildish
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, 2-3 path turn, weakened last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Best Man Speech
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped twice start, inside turn,angled out upper stretch,2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Oscar Nominee
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped, steadied start, showed little

ENTRY.NAME: Pete's Legacy
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Tigger Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost ground, mild gain late

ENTRY.NAME: Drinking Tour
ENTRY.OWNER: Hepp James and Reiman Peter S
ENTRY.COMMENT: crowded start, 3 wide turn, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: It's On
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke inward, 3-4 wide turn, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Cloey Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: clearly the best, driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARL G hesitated at the break, moved up to contention from outside, lugged in approaching the bend, jostled with READTHETRANSCRIPT, was steadied, progressed just off the inside, gained the rail nearing the quarter pole and edged ahead the last furlong. STOSH pressed from between horses, was three then four wide taking the turn, lacked the extra needed deep stretch but got up for second near the wire. PEACOCK MAN vied for the early lead from inside, moved ahead on the bend but slowly wore down just off the rail in the lane. PACHI prominent from outside from the beginning, lost considerable ground four to six wide through the turn, steadily closed the gap through the stretch but was too late. SHANGHAI SILVER forwardly placed between rivals, was just off the rail on the bend, swung out five wide for a clear path in the lane and could only make up minor ground in the waning yards. READTHETRANSCRIPT chased from between foes, was jostled by CARL G approaching the turn, forced in some, checked off WARNING LABEL'S heels and faded. BAM BAM CAM was hustled along to contest the pace between horses, began to yield before finishing a half mile and steadily gave way in the lane. WARNING LABEL was a contender from inside for two furlongs then quickly gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Peacock Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, weakened stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Warning Label
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, thru early

ENTRY.NAME: Bam Bam Cam
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between, 2-3 path turn, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Readthetranscript
ENTRY.COMMENT: jostled, checked off heels 7/16s

ENTRY.NAME: Shanghai Silver
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide 1/4, angled 5 wide into stretch, not enough late

ENTRY.NAME: Stosh
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed between, 3-4 wide turn, mild bid between, got 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Carl G
ENTRY.COMMENT: jostled, steadied 7/16s, rail bid, edged ahead last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Pachi
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-6 wide turn, gaining

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 11500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIL BIT TIPSEY rated off the early speed, was just off the inside on the bend, fanned out behind KIANA'S LOVE entering the lane, altered outside that one with a furlong to go, took the advantage approaching the final sixteenth, soon moved clear and prevailed under a mild drive. KIANA'S LOVE contested the pace from outside, was three wide through the turn, led briefly between rivals just after entering the last eighth but did not have enough left in the late going. BEIRUT BEAUTY had a poor start, was settled outside, commenced her bid after a quarter mile, lost ground widest through the bend, threatened with a furlong to go, leveled off the final furlong but moved clear for third. LINDALOUIMAGE chased from between rivals, retreated two wide on the turn, fanned out some for the drive, rallied upper stretch, also failed to sustain her bid the last eighth but improved position deep stretch outside weakening horses. GHAALEB'S APPEAL also had a poor start, advanced from inside on the bend, reached a striking position upper stretch, altered out for a clear path inside the final eighth and leveled off in the waning yards. LIFE OF SATURDAYS well placed from inside, flattened out the last furlong. AUNT STELLA faded from between horses early on and had little to offer for the drive. PLAY TWENTY disputed the pace between horses from the early going but gave way the final eighth.

ENTRY.NAME: Lil Bit Tipsey
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path turn, altered out 1/8, led inside 1/8, mild drive

ENTRY.NAME: Beirut Beauty
ENTRY.COMMENT: poor start, settled outside, 3-5 wide turn, mild bid

ENTRY.COMMENT: poor start, inside turn, altered out inside 1/8

ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, flattened out last 1/8

ENTRY.COMMENT: speed between, 2 wide turn, gave way last 1/8

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROAD GAME rated outside the early speed, took the lead into the bend, moved clear, lengthened command along the rail in the lane and kept CHICKS FOR FREE at bay under steady handling. CHICKS FOR FREE broke inward, was steadied to avoid CHANGE DIRECTION, advanced from outside to moved clear for second on the turn, angled in some for the stretch run, leveled off in the late going but lasted for the place. R H SMOAKEM prominent from inside, did not keep up on the bend, began to swing out for racing room nearing the end of a half mile and rallied belatedly four wide the last furlong. DEVIL'S RULE in contention early toward the outside, advanced two wide on the turn, slowly yielded in the lane but was easily best of the others. W W RUSSIAN GOLD chased from between horses and faded three wide on the bend. CAMPAIGN SPY also between rivals early, had the rail on the turn, angled out some for a clear path midstretch and had little to offer. CHANGE DIRECTION was reluctant to load, was widest taking the turn and had no late bid. KING TITO broke alertly but gave way from inside into the bend.

ENTRY.COMMENT: angled out 1/4, rallied belatedly 4 wide

ENTRY.COMMENT: inside turn, angled out 1/8, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 71. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 24000. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR WAIVER CLAIMING OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $12,500 FOR HORSES W HICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GHAALEB'S RANGER reluctant to load, was rated from inside, roused along the rail on the bend, altered out for a clear path nearing the final sixteenth and got up in the final strides. CANDY LOOKER quickly sprinted away from rest, showed the way staying off the rail, lugged in to gain the rail as she began to wear down inside the last eighth and was outfinished. MOON PIES IMAGE rated from outside, lost ground four wide through the bend, gradually drifted out upper stretch, was corrected, rallied in the late going but began to drift out again in the waning yards. GHAALEB'S CITY chased from between rivals, moved ahead for second while three wide on the turn but flattened out the final furlong. SHINE DOWN was away slowly, was hustled up to contention from inside, her rider lost her riding crop while between horses on the bend and she flattened out for the drive.

ENTRY.COMMENT: away slowly, rider lost riding crop while 2 wide turn

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 81. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 16500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Si nce May 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOT AGAIN JACKIE settled outside, circled horses while five wide on the bend, was crowded leaving the quarter pole, moved clear of the rest approaching the final sixteenth and held sway. BUREAU was bumped a few strides from the gate, settled inside, rallied along the rail in the lane, gained second near the sixteenth marker then could only make up minor ground on NOT AGAIN JACKIE in the waning yards. MAC PANDOWDY in contention early three wide, was shuffled back on the bend, lost ground fanning six wide into the stretch and rallied belatedly. LASTFORTINOFAMILY settled at the back, was just off the rail on the turn, lost considerable ground swinging out widest for the drive and also showed a willingness to run deep stretch. TAPIT SAM was a factor between rivals on the backstretch, was forced into NOT AGAIN JACKIE leaving the quarter pole, angled outside that one upper stretch and finished evenly. FEVER NATION contested the pace outside MUD ISLAND and was gradually forced out by that one as he began to wear down in the lane. FULL MAGAZINE was bumped and forced into BUREAU at the break, gained an easy striking position two wide on the bend, altered in some as MUD ISLAND came out upper stretch and slowly yielded. MUD ISLAND broke inward, starting a chain reaction of bumping, was soon disputing the pace from inside and gradually drifted out as he began to wear down in the stretch.

ENTRY.OWNER: Pohl Dennis and Gavilsky II Lawrence J
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, saved ground, mild gain late
